Shipments from a Vendor/Supplier or Customer (Return) location, direct toPlant,
Distribution Center, Warehouse, Customer, etc. are examples of which of the following
movement types?
A. Inbound Shipments
B. Outbound Shipments
C. Interplant Shipments
D. None of the above.
Answer: A
TMS has a collaborative network of the following:
A. Carrier
B. Vendor
C. Customer
D. Both A and B.
Answer: D
TMS can be used to manage which of the following transportation modes?
A. Truckload
B. Less than truckload (LTL)
C. Intermodal
D. All of the above.
Answer: D
